136
00:06:20,141 --> 00:06:24,540
And so after I finished reading the passage,

137
00:06:24,540 --> 00:06:28,139
I was supposed to give a speech about the topic

138
00:06:28,139 --> 00:06:29,847
that I just read

139
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:32,423
which was about hope.

140
00:06:32,423 --> 00:06:35,006
And so I stared at the inmates.

141
00:06:35,956 --> 00:06:38,043
They had their arms crossed.

142
00:06:38,043 --> 00:06:40,575
They were staring right back at me.

143
00:06:40,575 --> 00:06:43,186
Some of them had these really negative looks on their face.

144
00:06:43,186 --> 00:06:44,229
You can imagine.

145
00:06:44,229 --> 00:06:48,883
So I started giving a speech that I made up on the spot.

146
00:06:48,883 --> 00:06:51,376
I had no idea what I was going to say.

147
00:06:51,376 --> 00:06:54,709
So I said this, "Do you believe in God?"

148
00:06:56,938 --> 00:07:01,045
And a bunch of the inmates kind of went, "Yeah."

149
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:02,630
I then paused.

150
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:05,263
I said, "Does God believe in you?"

151
00:07:05,263 --> 00:07:09,287
And a couple more inmates said, "Yeah."

152
00:07:09,287 --> 00:07:12,771
Then I said this, "Well if you don't believe in yourself,

153
00:07:12,771 --> 00:07:17,163
"then you might have to question your faith."

154
00:07:17,163 --> 00:07:20,043
I paused again for a few seconds.

155
00:07:20,043 --> 00:07:23,275
And I felt a sense of calmness and peace

156
00:07:23,275 --> 00:07:25,025
and love in my heart.

157
00:07:26,243 --> 00:07:29,770
Almost like this public speaking handicap

158
00:07:29,770 --> 00:07:32,550
