165
00:07:50,587 --> 00:07:53,920
And I saw one man's angry eyebrows rise.

166
00:07:56,223 --> 00:07:57,647
I'll never forget that.

167
00:07:57,647 --> 00:08:00,403
Another one smiled at me.

168
00:08:00,403 --> 00:08:02,237
Actually it was the one with the crazy tattoo that said,

169
00:08:02,237 --> 00:08:03,878
I can't say it, okay.

170
00:08:03,878 --> 00:08:06,577
And another one looked up at the ceiling

171
00:08:06,577 --> 00:08:10,380
as if there was some kind of sense of temporary relief.

172
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:13,768
It was a eunuch experience for me.

173
00:08:13,768 --> 00:08:17,101
The only thing I can remember saying is,

174
00:08:19,713 --> 00:08:20,713
"Thank you."

175
00:08:21,905 --> 00:08:24,572
I paused and my heart opened up.

176
00:08:26,517 --> 00:08:30,823
I actually said this too, "You need not worry

177
00:08:30,823 --> 00:08:33,208
"as God already knows what's gonna happen.

178
00:08:33,208 --> 00:08:36,658
"And that should really give you peace of mind

179
00:08:36,658 --> 00:08:40,222
"and instill a sense of self-worth and confidence

180
00:08:40,222 --> 00:08:43,125
"and happiness and hope in your heart."

181
00:08:43,125 --> 00:08:44,625
So since that day,

182
00:08:46,091 --> 00:08:50,258
